{"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerLock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerUnlock()"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"StaticRWLockProtocol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib20StaticRWLockProtocolP","symbolKind":"protocol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Take a look at the following example:"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["  GStaticRWLock rwlock = G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock (&rwlock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&rwlock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_lock (&rwlock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index + 1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&rwlock);","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_get()"},{"type":"text","text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"code":"my_array_set()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function) will only be allowed once at a time","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Most of the time, writers should have precedence over readers. That","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"means, for this implementation, that as soon as a writer wants to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock the data, no other reader is allowed to lock the data, whereas,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of course, the readers that already have locked the data are allowed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to finish their operation. As soon as the last reader unlocks the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"data, the writer will lock it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Even though ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the following functions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_rw_lock_* functions can be used even if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" has not been called. Then they do nothing, apart"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from g_static_rw_lock_*_trylock, which does nothing but returning "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A read-write lock has a higher overhead than a mutex. For example, both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()"},{"text":" have","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to lock and unlock a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", so it takes at least twice the time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to lock and unlock a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that it does to lock and unlock a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":". So only data structures that are accessed by multiple","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"readers, and which keep the lock for a considerable time justify a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The above example most probably would fare better with a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"]},{"title":"Conforming Types","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"],"type":"conformingTypes"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol"},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"text":" struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"only one writer may write at a time."}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockRef":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticRWLockRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockref","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef","title":"StaticRWLockRef","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only one writer may write at a time."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticRWLockRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/writerUnlock()":{"title":"writerUnlock()","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/writerunlock()","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerUnlock()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writerUnlock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlocks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":". If a thread is waiting to lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" for writing and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all locks for reading have been unlocked, the waiting thread is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"woken up and can lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing. If no thread is waiting to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for writing, and some thread or threads are waiting to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading, the waiting threads are woken up and can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading."}],"deprecated":true},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/readerTrylock()":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerTrylock()","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"readerTrylock()","deprecated":true,"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readerTrylock","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tries to lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading. If "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is already locked for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"writing by another thread or if another thread is already waiting to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" for writing, immediately returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Otherwise locks"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading and returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". This lock has to be unlocked by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/readertrylock()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/free()":{"deprecated":true,"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/free()","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"free","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"type":"topic","title":"free()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/free()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Releases all resources allocated to "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/init_()":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/init_()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/init_()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"text":" must be initialized with this function before it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be used. Alternatively you can initialize it with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"title":"init_()","deprecated":true},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"text":" struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only one writer may write at a time.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticRWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"StaticRWLockProtocol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/readerLock()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Locks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading. There may be unlimited concurrent locks for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reading of a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"text":" at the same time.  If ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is already","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"locked for writing by another thread or if another thread is already"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"waiting to lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing, this function will block until"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is unlocked by the other writing thread and no other writing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads want to lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":". This lock has to be unlocked by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"deprecated":true,"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"readerLock()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"readerLock","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/readerlock()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/PointerWrapper":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Protocol for GLib types that wrap pointers."}],"title":"PointerWrapper","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/pointerwrapper","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/writerLock()":{"title":"writerLock()","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/writerlock()","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerLock()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writerLock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Locks ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" is already locked for writing or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reading by other threads, this function will block until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"completely unlocked and then lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for writing. While this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions waits to lock "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":", no other thread can lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reading. When "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is locked for writing, no other thread can lock","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" (neither for reading nor writing). This lock has to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unlocked by ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"deprecated":true},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Mutex":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mutex","title":"Mutex","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"access.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticMutex":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutex"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticmutex","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticMutex","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"StaticMutex","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" works like a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/readerUnlock()":{"title":"readerUnlock()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerUnlock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/readerUnlock()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlocks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"type":"text","text":". If a thread waits to lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for writing and all","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"locks for reading have been unlocked, the waiting thread is woken up"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and can lock "},{"code":"lock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for writing.","type":"text"}],"deprecated":true,"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlockprotocol\/readerunlock()","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLock":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":" struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only one writer may write at a time."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlock","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticRWLock","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLock"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"StaticRWLock"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/StaticRWLockProtocol/writerTrylock()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol\/writerTrylock()","abstract":[{"text":"Tries to lock ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" for writing. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" is already locked (for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"either reading or writing) by another thread, it immediately returns","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":". Otherwise it locks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lock"},{"text":" for writing and returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". This"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock has to be unlocked by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"deprecated":true,"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"writerTrylock","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/staticrw